3Cpath id=\"DejaVuSans-75\" d=\"M 544 1381 \n","L 544 3500 \n","L 1119 3500 \n","L 1119 1403 \n","Q 1119 906 1312 657 \n","Q 1506 409 1894 409 \n","Q 2359 409 2629 706 \n","Q 2900 1003 2900 1516 \n","L 2900 3500 \n","L 3475 3500 \n","L 3475 0 \n","L 2900 0 \n","L 2900 538 \n","Q 2691 219 2414 64 \n","Q 2138 -91 1772 -91 \n","Q 1169 -91 856 284 \n","Q 544 659 544 1381 \n","z\n","M 1991 3584 \n","L 1991 3584 \n","z\n","\" transform=\"scale(0.015625)\"/\u003E\n","      \u003C/defs\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-67\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-72\" x=\"63.476562\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-61\" x=\"104.589844\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-64\" x=\"165.869141\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-20\" x=\"229.345703\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-6f\" x=\"261.132812\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-66\" x=\"322.314453\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-20\" x=\"357.519531\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-72\" x=\"389.306641\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-65\" x=\"428.169922\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-6c\" x=\"489.693359\"/\u003E\n","      \u003Cuse xlink:href=\"#DejaVuSans-75\" x=\"517.476562\"/\u003E\n","     \u003C/g\u003E\n","    \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"line2d_31\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 56.463068 139.5 \n","L 182.483654 139.5 \n","L 184.078852 13.5 \n","L 310.099432 13.5 \n","L 310.099432 13.5 \n","\" clip-path=\"url(#p5628208642)\" style=\"fill: none; stroke: #1f77b4; stroke-width: 1.5; stroke-linecap: square\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"patch_3\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 43.78125 145.8 \n","L 43.78125 7.2 \n","\" style=\"fill: none; stroke: #000000; stroke-width: 0.8; stroke-linejoin: miter; stroke-linecap: square\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"patch_4\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 322.78125 145.8 \n","L 322.78125 7.2 \n","\" style=\"fill: none; stroke: #000000; stroke-width: 0.8; stroke-linejoin: miter; stroke-linecap: square\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"patch_5\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 43.78125 145.8 \n","L 322.78125 145.8 \n","\" style=\"fill: none; stroke: #000000; stroke-width: 0.8; stroke-linejoin: miter; stroke-linecap: square\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"patch_6\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 43.78125 7.2 \n","L 322.78125 7.2 \n","\" style=\"fill: none; stroke: #000000; stroke-width: 0.8; stroke-linejoin: miter; stroke-linecap: square\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","  \u003C/g\u003E\n"," \u003C/g\u003E\n"," \u003Cdefs\u003E\n","  \u003CclipPath id=\"p5628208642\"\u003E\n","   \u003Crect x=\"43.78125\" y=\"7.2\" width=\"279\" height=\"138.6\"/\u003E\n","  \u003C/clipPath\u003E\n"," \u003C/defs\u003E\n","\u003C/svg\u003E\n"],"text/plain":["\u003CFigure size 500x250 with 1 Axes\u003E"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["# 让 PyTorch 自动算出 ReLU 输出 y 对输入 x 的导数（梯度），并把结果存在 x.grad 里。\n","# y.backward(...)：触发「反向传播」（深度学习算梯度的核心机制）。可以理解为：告诉 PyTorch “我要算 y 相对于所有能影响它的张量（这里就是 x）的导数”。\n","# torch.ones_like(x)：给反向传播 “递一个计算规则”。\n","# torch.ones_like(x) 会生成一个和 x 长得一模一样的张量（形状、数据类型都相同），但所有元素都是 1。\n","# 为什么需要它？因为 y 是和 x 一样的 “数组”（比如有 100 个元素），不是单个数字。全 1 的张量表示：对 y 中每一个元素的梯度 “平等求和”，最终算出 x 每个位置的梯度（简单说：保证梯度计算结果和 x 形状匹配，不会报错）。\n","# 新手可以记死：只要 y 是数组型张量（不是单个标量），backward() 里就传 torch.ones_like(x) 准没错。\n","y.backward(torch.ones_like(x), retain_graph=True) # retain_graph=True：“保留计算图不删除”。\n","# x.detach()：给绘图函数 “喂横轴数据”。\n","# x 是 PyTorch 张量，还带着 “梯度追踪” 的标记，绘图库（比如 Matplotlib）不认识这种带标记的张量。\n","# detach() 就是 “撕掉标记”，把 x 变成普通的数值数组，绘图库就能用了（简单说：让 x 能被画图）。\n","d2l.plot(x.detach(), x.grad, 'x', 'grad of relu', figsize=(5, 2.5)) # 'grad of relu'：给纵轴加标签，图的左侧会显示 “grad of relu”，别人一看就知道纵轴是 ReLU 的梯度。"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"e1b426b7","metadata":{},"source":"\u003Cp\u003E使用ReLU的原因是，它求导表现得特别好：要么让参数消失，要么让参数通过。\n这使得优化表现得更好，并且ReLU减轻了困扰以往神经网络的梯度消失问题（稍后将详细介绍）。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E注意，ReLU函数有许多变体，包括\u003Cem\u003E参数化ReLU\u003C/em\u003E（Parameterized ReLU，\u003Cem\u003EpReLU\u003C/em\u003E）\n函数。\n该变体为ReLU添加了一个线性项，因此即使参数是负的，某些信息仍然可以通过：\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E$$\\operatorname{pReLU}(x) = \\max(0, x) + \\alpha \\min(0, x).$$\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003E\n\u003Ca id=\"sigmoid函数\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#sigmoid%E5%87%BD%E6%95%B0\"\u003E\u003C/a\u003Esigmoid函数\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E[\u003Cstrong\u003E对于一个定义域在$\\mathbb{R}$中的输入，\n\u003Cem\u003Esigmoid函数\u003C/em\u003E将输入变换为区间(0, 1)上的输出\u003C/strong\u003E]。\n因此，sigmoid通常称为\u003Cem\u003E挤压函数\u003C/em\u003E（squashing function）：\n它将范围（-inf, inf）中的任意输入压缩到区间（0, 1）中的某个值：\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E(\u003Cstrong\u003E$$\\operatorname{sigmoid}(x) = \\frac{1}{1 + \\exp(-x)}.$$\u003C/strong\u003E)\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E在最早的神经网络中，科学家们感兴趣的是对“激发”或“不激发”的生物神经元进行建模。\n因此，这一领域的先驱可以一直追溯到人工神经元的发明者麦卡洛克和皮茨，他们专注于阈值单元。\n阈值单元在其输入低于某个阈值时取值0，当输入超过阈值时取值1。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E当人们逐渐关注到到基于梯度的学习时，\nsigmoid函数是一个自然的选择，因为它是一个平滑的、可微的阈值单元近似。\n当我们想要将输出视作二元分类问题的概率时，\nsigmoid仍然被广泛用作输出单元上的激活函数\n（sigmoid可以视为softmax的特例）。\n然而，sigmoid在隐藏层中已经较少使用，\n它在大部分时候被更简单、更容易训练的ReLU所取代。\n在后面关于循环神经网络的章节中，我们将描述利用sigmoid单元来控制时序信息流的架构。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E下面，我们绘制sigmoid函数。\n注意，当输入接近0时，sigmoid函数接近线性变换。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ESigmoid 函数是深度学习中经典的激活函数，核心作用是把任意实数映射到 0~1 之间，常用来做二分类任务的输出层（比如判断 “是 / 否”“正 / 负”）。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EThe Sigmoid function is a classic activation Function in deep learning.Its core function is to map any real number to the range between 0 and 1.It is commonly used in the output later for binary classification tasks,such as determining\"yes/no\"or\"positive/negative\".\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ESigmoid 能用来干啥？\n二分类输出层：最核心用途！比如判断 “图片里是不是猫”：输出≈1 代表 “是猫”，输出≈0 代表 “不是猫”，0.5 是分界点；\n早期神经网络的隐藏层：在 ReLU 出现前，Sigmoid 是隐藏层的主流激活函数（引入非线性），但现在几乎被 ReLU 取代；\n概率表示：输出值可以直接理解为 “概率”（比如输出 0.8，代表有 80% 的概率是正类）。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat is SIgmoid used for? represents\"is not a cat,\"with 0.5 serving as the decision boundary.\nOutput layer for Binary Classification:This is its most core application!For example,when determining\"is there a cat in the picture?\":an output ≈0 represents\"is not a cat,\"with 0.5 serving as the decision boundary.\nHidden Layers in Early Neural Networks:Before the emergence of Re:U,Sigmoid was the mainstream activation function for hidden layers(introducing non-linearity).However,it has now been almost entirely replaced by ReLU.\nProbability Representation:The output value can be directy interpreted as a probability.For instance,an outputof 0.8 implies an 80probability of being the positive class.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ESigmoid 的致命缺点\n梯度消失问题：\nSigmoid 的导数最大值只有 0.25（在 x=0 处）；当 x 很大 / 很小（比如 x\u0026gt;5 或 x\u0026lt;-5），导数几乎为 0；\n深层网络中，梯度从输出层往输入层传时，会越传越小（趋近于 0），导致前面的层学不到东西（梯度消失）。\n输出不是 0 均值：\nSigmoid 输出永远 \u0026gt; 0，导致隐藏层的输出都是正数，反向传播时梯度要么全正、要么全负，参数更新效率低；\n计算成本高：\n涉及指数运算（e^-x），比 ReLU 的 “只比大小” 计算慢。\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EThe Fatal Flaws of Sigmoid\nThe Vanishing Gradient Problem:\nTeh maximum value of the Sigmoid derivative is only 0.25(at x=0)when x is very large or very small(e.g.x\u0026gt;5 or x\u0026lt;-5),the derivate is almost 0.in deep networks,as gradients propagate backwords from the output layer to the input layer,they become increasingly smaller(approaching 0).This causes the earlier layers to fail to learn(the vanishing gradient problem).\nOutputs are not Zero-centered:\nSigmoid outputs are always positive(\u0026gt;0).this results in hiddenlayeroutputs being strictily positive.During backpropagation.gradients will be either all posotove or all negative,leadingto ineffcient parameter updates(often described as a \"zig-zag'movement in optimization).\nHigh Computational Cost:\nIt involves exponential operations($e^-x$),which are computationally slower compared to ReLU's simple comparison logic(\"just comparing magnitudes\").\u003C/p\u003E"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"0ef9ed8b","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/svg+xml":["\u003C?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" standalone=\"no\"?\u003E\n","\u003C!DOCTYPE svg PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD SVG 1.1//EN\"\n","  \"http://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/1.1/DTD/svg11.dtd\"\u003E\n","\u003Csvg xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" width=\"329.98125pt\" height=\"183.35625pt\" viewBox=\"0 0 329.98125 183.35625\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" version=\"1.1\"\u003E\n"," \u003Cmetadata\u003E\n","  \u003Crdf:RDF xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\" xmlns:cc=\"http://creativecommons.org/ns#\" xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\"\u003E\n","   \u003Ccc:Work\u003E\n","    \u003Cdc:type rdf:resource=\"http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/StillImage\"/\u003E\n","    \u003Cdc:date\u003E2026-03-19T04:06:32.435658\u003C/dc:date\u003E\n","    \u003Cdc:format\u003Eimage/svg+xml\u003C/dc:format\u003E\n","    \u003Cdc:creator\u003E\n","     \u003Ccc:Agent\u003E\n","      \u003Cdc:title\u003EMatplotlib v3.7.5, https://matplotlib.org/\u003C/dc:title\u003E\n","     \u003C/cc:Agent\u003E\n","    \u003C/dc:creator\u003E\n","   \u003C/cc:Work\u003E\n","  \u003C/rdf:RDF\u003E\n"," \u003C/metadata\u003E\n"," \u003Cdefs\u003E\n","  \u003Cstyle type=\"text/css\"\u003E*{stroke-linejoin: round; stroke-linecap: butt}\u003C/style\u003E\n"," \u003C/defs\u003E\n"," \u003Cg id=\"figure_1\"\u003E\n","  \u003Cg id=\"patch_1\"\u003E\n","   \u003Cpath d=\"M 0 183.35625 \n","L 329.98125 183.35625 \n","L 329.98125 0 \n","L 0 0 \n","z\n","\" style=\"fill: #ffffff\"/\u003E\n","  \u003C/g\u003E\n","  \u003Cg id=\"axes_1\"\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"patch_2\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cpath d=\"M 43.78125 145.8 \n","L 322.78125 145.8 \n","L 322.78125 7.2 \n","L 43.78125 7.2 \n","z\n","\" style=\"fill: #ffffff\"/\u003E\n","   \u003C/g\u003E\n","   \u003Cg id=\"matplotlib.axis_1\"\u003E\n","    \u003Cg id=\"xtick_1\"\u003E\n","  